\section{Dependencies}{

\strong{data.table} (>= 1.14.0) is used for all tabular data operations.
\strong{parallel} provides \code{detectCores()} for the GDS backend thread count.
\strong{stats} provides \code{lm()}, \code{cor()}, and \code{residuals()}.

Optional Bioconductor packages extend the package to large panels:
\strong{SNPRelate} and \strong{gdsfmt} enable the GDS streaming backend for panels
with more than 2 million SNPs; \strong{VariantAnnotation}, \strong{GenomeInfoDb},
\strong{SummarizedExperiment}, \strong{Biostrings}, and \strong{S4Vectors} enable VCF
input.
}

